GeoApp:
-------
1. Basic node server with express is created 

2.


https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Geolocation_API/Using_the_Geolocation_API
3. The Geolocation API allows the user to provide their location to web applications if they so desire. For privacy reasons, the user is asked for permission to report location information.

WebExtensions that wish to use the Geolocation object must add the "geolocation" permission to their manifest. The user's operating system will prompt the user to allow location access the first time it is requested.
Secure context of Geolocation API :
---------------------------------
This feature is available only in secure contexts (HTTPS), in some or all supporting browsers.

4: Server host static html file on the client--> client located the geolocation sends that to the server using POST and fetch method 
    --> server receives it and send the response back to the client (for a complete handshake and data is exchanged)
